{
  "work_slug": "alices-adventures-in-wonderland-by-lewis-carroll-5",
  "work_title": "Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (version 4)",
  "work_author": "Lewis Carroll",
  "audio_file": "audio-03",
  "audio_url": "https://archive.org/download/alices_adventures_1005_librivox/wonderland_03_carroll.mp3",
  "chapter_title": "03 - A Caucus-race and a Long Tale",
  "reader_name": "Eric Leach",
  "para_gap_threshold": 1.54,
  "page_num": 3,
  "page_total": 3,
  "page_start_sec": 496.0,
  "page_end_sec": 588.38,
  "segments": [
    {
      "start": 496.0,
      "end": 496.7,
      "text": "\"Hold your tongue,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 496.72,
      "end": 496.84,
      "text": "Ma!\""
    },
    {
      "start": 497.04,
      "end": 498.67,
      "text": "said the young Crab, a little snappishly."
    },
    {
      "start": 499.392,
      "end": 501.22,
      "text": "\"You're enough to try the patience of an oyster!\""
    },
    {
      "start": 502.99,
      "end": 504.9,
      "text": "\"I wish I had our Dinah here,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 505.0,
      "end": 505.74,
      "text": "I know I do!\""
    },
    {
      "start": 506.0,
      "end": 506.9,
      "text": "said Alice aloud,"
    },
    {
      "start": 507.18,
      "end": 508.66,
      "text": "addressing nobody in particular."
    },
    {
      "start": 509.408,
      "end": 510.32,
      "text": "\"She'd soon fetch it back!\""
    },
    {
      "start": 511.96,
      "end": 512.94,
      "text": "\"And who is Dinah,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 513.08,
      "end": 515.04,
      "text": "if I might venture to ask the question?\""
    },
    {
      "start": 515.45,
      "end": 516.38,
      "text": "said the Lory."
    },
    {
      "start": 517.536,
      "end": 518.66,
      "text": "Alice replied eagerly,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 518.66,
      "end": 520.88,
      "text": "for she was always ready to talk about her pet:"
    },
    {
      "start": 521.792,
      "end": 522.54,
      "text": "\"Dinah's our cat."
    },
    {
      "start": 522.68,
      "end": 525.02,
      "text": "And she's such a capital one for catching mice,"
    },
    {
      "start": 525.06,
      "end": 525.8,
      "text": "you ca'n't think!"
    },
    {
      "start": 526.4,
      "end": 526.68,
      "text": "And oh,"
    },
    {
      "start": 526.72,
      "end": 528.52,
      "text": "I wish you could see her after the birds!"
    },
    {
      "start": 528.76,
      "end": 528.94,
      "text": "Why,"
    },
    {
      "start": 529.02,
      "end": 531.22,
      "text": "she'll eat a little bird as soon as look at it!\""
    },
    {
      "start": 532.2,
      "end": 535.14,
      "text": "This speech caused a remarkable sensation among the party.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 535.48,
      "end": 537.0,
      "text": "Some of the birds hurried off at once;"
    },
    {
      "start": 537.4,
      "end": 540.54,
      "text": "one old Magpie began wrapping itself up very carefully,"
    },
    {
      "start": 540.74,
      "end": 541.28,
      "text": "remarking,"
    },
    {
      "start": 541.5,
      "end": 543.48,
      "text": "\"I really must be getting home;"
    },
    {
      "start": 543.6,
      "end": 545.34,
      "text": "the night-air doesn't suit my throat!\""
    },
    {
      "start": 546.08,
      "end": 548.9,
      "text": "and a Canary called out in a trembling voice to its children,"
    },
    {
      "start": 549.64,
      "end": 549.96,
      "text": "\"Come away,"
    },
    {
      "start": 550.06,
      "end": 550.58,
      "text": "my dears!"
    },
    {
      "start": 550.69,
      "end": 552.56,
      "text": "It's high time you were all in bed!\""
    },
    {
      "start": 553.64,
      "end": 554.72,
      "text": "On various pretexts"
    },
    {
      "start": 554.84,
      "end": 555.68,
      "text": "they all moved off,"
    },
    {
      "start": 555.8,
      "end": 557.16,
      "text": "and Alice was soon left alone."
    },
    {
      "start": 557.92,
      "end": 559.64,
      "text": "\"I wish I hadn't mentioned Dinah!\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 559.66,
      "end": 561.64,
      "text": "she said to herself in a melancholy tone."
    },
    {
      "start": 562.24,
      "end": 563.82,
      "text": "\"Nobody seems to like her, down here,"
    },
    {
      "start": 563.94,
      "end": 565.88,
      "text": "and I'm sure she's the best cat in the world!"
    },
    {
      "start": 566.42,
      "end": 566.78,
      "text": "Oh,"
    },
    {
      "start": 566.88,
      "end": 567.82,
      "text": "my dear Dinah!"
    },
    {
      "start": 567.86,
      "end": 569.9,
      "text": "I wonder if I shall ever see you any more!\""
    },
    {
      "start": 570.78,
      "end": 572.62,
      "text": "And here poor Alice began to cry again,"
    },
    {
      "start": 572.8,
      "end": 575.18,
      "text": "for she felt very lonely and low-spirited."
    },
    {
      "start": 576.02,
      "end": 576.7,
      "text": "In a little while,"
    },
    {
      "start": 576.8,
      "end": 577.02,
      "text": "however,"
    },
    {
      "start": 577.2,
      "end": 580.16,
      "text": "she again heard a little pattering of footsteps in the distance,"
    },
    {
      "start": 580.36,
      "end": 581.49,
      "text": "and she looked up eagerly,"
    },
    {
      "start": 581.6,
      "end": 584.02,
      "text": "half hoping that the Mouse had changed his mind,"
    },
    {
      "start": 584.1,
      "end": 585.78,
      "text": "and was coming back to finish his story."
    },
    {
      "start": 587.52,
      "end": 588.38,
      "text": "End of chapter 3"
    }
  ]
}